  33. ‌let rec select_addr exp =
  34.   let default = (Alinear exp, 0) in
  35.   match exp with
  36.     Cconst_symbol (s, _) when not !Clflags.dlcode ->
  37.       (Asymbol s, 0)
  38.   | Cop((Caddi | Caddv | Cadda), [arg; Cconst_int (m, _)], _)
  39.   | Cop((Caddi | Caddv | Cadda), [Cconst_int (m, _); arg], _) ->
  40.       let (a, n) = select_addr arg in
  41.       if Misc.no_overflow_add n m then (a, n + m) else default
  42.   | Cop(Csubi, [arg; Cconst_int (m, _)], _) ->
  43. ‌      let (a, n) = select_addr arg in
  44.       if Misc.no_overflow_sub n m then (a, n - m) else default
  45.   | Cop(Clsl, [arg; Cconst_int((1|2|3 as shift), _)], _) ->
  46.       begin match select_addr arg with
  47.       | (Alinear e, n) when Misc.no_overflow_lsl n shift ->
  48.           (Ascale(e, 1 lsl shift), n lsl shift)
  49.       | _ -> default
  50.       end
  51.   | Cop(Cmuli, [arg; Cconst_int((2|4|8 as mult), _)], _)
  52.   | Cop(Cmuli, [Cconst_int((2|4|8 as mult), _); arg], _) ->
  53.       begin match select_addr arg with
  54.       | (Alinear e, n) when Misc.no_overflow_mul n mult ->
  55.           (Ascale(e, mult), n * mult)
  56.       | _ -> default
  57.       end
  58.   | Cop((Caddi | Caddv | Cadda), [arg1; arg2], _) ->
  59.       begin match (select_addr arg1, select_addr arg2) with
  60.           ((Alinear e1, n1), (Alinear e2, n2))
  61.           when Misc.no_overflow_add n1 n2 ->
  62.               (Aadd(e1, e2), n1 + n2)
  63.         | ((Alinear e1, n1), (Ascale(e2, scale), n2))
  64.         | ((Ascale(e2, scale), n2), (Alinear e1, n1))
  65.           when Misc.no_overflow_add n1 n2 ->
  66.               (Ascaledadd(e1, e2, scale), n1 + n2)
  67.         | (_, (Ascale(e2, scale), n2)) ->
  68.               (Ascaledadd(arg1, e2, scale), n2)
  69.         | ((Ascale(e1, scale), n1), _) ->
  70.               (Ascaledadd(arg2, e1, scale), n1)
  71.         | _ ->
  72.               (Aadd(arg1, arg2), 0)
  73.       end
  74.   | _ -> default

  84. ‌let pseudoregs_for_operation op arg res =
  85.   match op with
  86.   (* Two-address binary operations: arg.(0) and res.(0) must be the same *)
  87.     Iintop(Iadd|Isub|Imul|Iand|Ior|Ixor) | Iaddf|Isubf|Imulf|Idivf ->
  88.       ([|res.(0); arg.(1)|], res)
  89.   (* One-address unary operations: arg.(0) and res.(0) must be the same *)
  90.   | Iintop_imm((Iadd|Isub|Imul|Iand|Ior|Ixor|Ilsl|Ilsr|Iasr), _)
  91.   | Iabsf | Inegf
  92.   | Ispecific(Ibswap (32|64)) ->
  93.       (res, res)
  94.   (* For xchg, args must be a register allowing access to high 8 bit register
  95.      (rax, rbx, rcx or rdx). Keep it simple, just force the argument in rax. *)
  96.   | Ispecific(Ibswap 16) ->
  97.       ([| rax |], [| rax |])
  98.   (* For imulq, first arg must be in rax, rax is clobbered, and result is in
  99.      rdx. *)
  100.   | Iintop(Imulh) ->
  101.       ([| rax; arg.(1) |], [| rdx |])
  102.   | Ispecific(Ifloatarithmem(_,_)) ->
  103.       let arg' = Array.copy arg in
  104.       arg'.(0) <- res.(0);
  105.       (arg', res)
  106.   (* For shifts with variable shift count, second arg must be in rcx *)
  107.   | Iintop(Ilsl|Ilsr|Iasr) ->
  108.       ([|res.(0); rcx|], res)
  109.   (* For div and mod, first arg must be in rax, rdx is clobbered,
  110.      and result is in rax or rdx respectively.
  111.      Keep it simple, just force second argument in rcx. *)
  112.   | Iintop(Idiv) ->
  113.       ([| rax; rcx |], [| rax |])
  114.   | Iintop(Imod) ->
  115.       ([| rax; rcx |], [| rdx |])
  116.   | Icompf cond ->
  117.       (* We need to temporarily store the result of the comparison in a
  118.          float register, but we don't want to clobber any of the inputs
  119.          if they would still be live after this operation -- so we
  120.          add a fresh register as both an input and output. We don't use
  121.          [destroyed_at_oper], because that forces us to choose a fixed
  122.          register, which makes it more likely an extra mov would be added
  123.          to transfer the argument to the fixed register. *)
  124.       let treg = Reg.create Float in
  125.       let _,is_swapped = float_cond_and_need_swap cond in
  126.       (if is_swapped then [| arg.(0); treg |] else [| treg; arg.(1) |])
  127.     , [| res.(0); treg |]
  128.   (* Other instructions are regular *)
  129.   | _ -> raise Use_default

  141. (* The selector class *)

  143. class selector = object (self)

  145. inherit Selectgen.selector_generic as super

  147. method! is_immediate op n =
  148.   match op with
  149.   | Iadd | Isub | Imul | Iand | Ior | Ixor | Icomp _ | Icheckbound ->
  150.       is_immediate n
  151.   | _ ->
  152.       super#is_immediate op n

  154. method is_immediate_test _cmp n = is_immediate n

  156. method! is_simple_expr e =
  157.   match e with
  158.   | Cop(Cextcall (fn, _, _, _), args, _)
  159.     when List.mem fn inline_ops ->
  160.       (* inlined ops are simple if their arguments are *)
  161.       List.for_all self#is_simple_expr args
  162.   | _ ->
  163.       super#is_simple_expr e

  165. method! effects_of e =
  166.   match e with
  167.   | Cop(Cextcall(fn, _, _, _), args, _)
  168.     when List.mem fn inline_ops ->
  169.       Selectgen.Effect_and_coeffect.join_list_map args self#effects_of
  170.   | _ ->
  171.       super#effects_of e

  173. method select_addressing _chunk exp =
  174.   let (a, d) = select_addr exp in
  175.   (* PR#4625: displacement must be a signed 32-bit immediate *)
  176.   if not (is_immediate d)
  177.   then (Iindexed 0, exp)
  178.   else match a with
  179.     | Asymbol s ->
  180.         (Ibased(s, d), Ctuple [])
  181.     | Alinear e ->
  182.         (Iindexed d, e)
  183.     | Aadd(e1, e2) ->
  184.         (Iindexed2 d, Ctuple[e1; e2])
  185.     | Ascale(e, scale) ->
  186.         (Iscaled(scale, d), e)
  187.     | Ascaledadd(e1, e2, scale) ->
  188.         (Iindexed2scaled(scale, d), Ctuple[e1; e2])

  190. method! select_store is_assign addr exp =
  191.   match exp with
  192.     Cconst_int (n, _dbg) when is_immediate n ->
  193.       (Ispecific(Istore_int(Nativeint.of_int n, addr, is_assign)), Ctuple [])
  194.   | (Cconst_natint (n, _dbg)) when is_immediate_natint n ->
  195.       (Ispecific(Istore_int(n, addr, is_assign)), Ctuple [])
  196.   | _ ->
  197.       super#select_store is_assign addr exp

  199. method! select_operation op args dbg =
  200.   match op with
  201.   (* Recognize the LEA instruction *)
  202.     Caddi | Caddv | Cadda | Csubi ->
  203.       begin match self#select_addressing Word_int (Cop(op, args, dbg)) with
  204.         (Iindexed _, _)
  205.       | (Iindexed2 0, _) -> super#select_operation op args dbg
  206.       | (addr, arg) -> (Ispecific(Ilea addr), [arg])
  207.       end
  208.   (* Recognize float arithmetic with memory. *)
  209.   | Caddf ->
  210.       self#select_floatarith true Iaddf Ifloatadd args
  211.   | Csubf ->
  212.       self#select_floatarith false Isubf Ifloatsub args
  213.   | Cmulf ->
  214.       self#select_floatarith true Imulf Ifloatmul args
  215.   | Cdivf ->
  216.       self#select_floatarith false Idivf Ifloatdiv args
  217.   | Cextcall("sqrt", _, _, false) ->
  218.      begin match args with
  219.        [Cop(Cload {memory_chunk=(Double as chunk)}, [loc], _dbg)] ->
  220. ‌         let (addr, arg) = self#select_addressing chunk loc in
  221.          (Ispecific(Ifloatsqrtf addr), [arg])
  222.      | [arg] ->
  223.          (Ispecific Isqrtf, [arg])
  224.      | _ ->
  225.          assert false
  226.      end
  227.   (* Recognize store instructions *)
  228.   | Cstore ((Word_int|Word_val as chunk), _init) ->
  229.       begin match args with
  230.         [loc; Cop(Caddi, [Cop(Cload _, [loc'], _); Cconst_int (n, _dbg)], _)]
  231.         when loc = loc' && is_immediate n ->
  232. ‌          let (addr, arg) = self#select_addressing chunk loc in
  233.           (Ispecific(Ioffset_loc(n, addr)), [arg])
  234.       | _ ->
  235.           super#select_operation op args dbg
  236.       end
  237.   | Cextcall("caml_bswap16_direct", _, _, _) ->
  238.       (Ispecific (Ibswap 16), args)
  239.   | Cextcall("caml_int32_direct_bswap", _, _, _) ->
  240.       (Ispecific (Ibswap 32), args)
  241.   | Cextcall("caml_int64_direct_bswap", _, _, _)
  242.   | Cextcall("caml_nativeint_direct_bswap", _, _, _) ->
  243.       (Ispecific (Ibswap 64), args)
  244.   (* Recognize sign extension *)
  245.   | Casr ->
  246.       begin match args with
  247.         [Cop(Clsl, [k; Cconst_int (32, _)], _); Cconst_int (32, _)] ->
  248.           (Ispecific Isextend32, [k])
  249.         | _ -> super#select_operation op args dbg
  250.       end
  251.   (* Recognize zero extension *)
  252.   | Cand ->
  253.     begin match args with
  254.     | [arg; Cconst_int (0xffff_ffff, _)]
  255.     | [arg; Cconst_natint (0xffff_ffffn, _)]
  256.     | [Cconst_int (0xffff_ffff, _); arg]
  257.     | [Cconst_natint (0xffff_ffffn, _); arg] ->
  258.       Ispecific Izextend32, [arg]
  259.     | _ -> super#select_operation op args dbg
  260.     end
  261.   | _ -> super#select_operation op args dbg

  263. (* Recognize float arithmetic with mem *)

  265. method select_floatarith commutative regular_op mem_op args =
  266.   match args with
  267.     [arg1; Cop(Cload {memory_chunk=(Double as chunk)}, [loc2], _)] ->
  268.       let (addr, arg2) = self#select_addressing chunk loc2 in
  269.       (Ispecific(Ifloatarithmem(mem_op, addr)),
  270.                  [arg1; arg2])
  271.   | [Cop(Cload {memory_chunk=(Double as chunk)}, [loc1], _); arg2]
  272.         when commutative ->
  273.       let (addr, arg1) = self#select_addressing chunk loc1 in
  274.       (Ispecific(Ifloatarithmem(mem_op, addr)),
  275.                  [arg2; arg1])
  276.   | [arg1; arg2] ->
  277.       (regular_op, [arg1; arg2])
  278.   | _ ->
  279.       assert false

  281. method! mark_c_tailcall =
  282.   contains_calls := true

  286. method! insert_op_debug env op dbg rs rd =
  287.   try
  288. ‌    let (rsrc, rdst) = pseudoregs_for_operation op rs rd in
  289.     self#insert_moves env rs rsrc;
  290.     self#insert_debug env (Iop op) dbg rsrc rdst;
  291.     self#insert_moves env rdst rd;
  292.     rd
  293.   with Use_default ->
  294.     super#insert_op_debug env op dbg rs rd

  296. end
